parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall intermittently, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle accelerates on its own intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and potentially causing a breakdown or accident.
symptoms: The engine cooling system fan motor fails

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket or valve cover gasket can cause engine oil leaks, coolant leaks, and engine damage, leading to a breakdown or accident.
symptoms: The head gasket or valve cover gasket fails

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to a breakdown or accident.
The failure of the thermostat can cause the engine to overheat or underheat, leading to engine damage or a breakdown.
symptoms: the thermostat needs to be replaced repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty lockup torque converter can cause chronic stalling, which can lead to accidents, especially when the vehicle stalls on a busy road or highway. This can also cause inconvenience and frustration to the driver.
symptoms: the vehicle hesitates or stutters before stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed rear main seal can cause oil leaks, which can lead to engine damage and potentially cause accidents due to loss of engine power or oil-slicked roads.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the rear of the engine
the engine oil level drops rapidly.
